<paragraph id="207B96733D74FF93FF1DFC3CFE5BFB71" blockId="7.[151,1437,905,1327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FF1DFC3CFEF9FB99" bold="true" box="[151,274,1013,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FEF4FC3FFDF3FB99" authorityName=": Brescovit" authorityYear="1997" box="[382,536,1013,1039]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FEF4FC3FFDF3FB99" box="[382,536,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Patrera ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FD6CFC3FFCAFFB99" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[742,836,1013,1039]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimar" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FD6CFC3FFCAFFB99" box="[742,836,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. dimar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FCC3FC3CFC6CFB99" bold="true" box="[841,903,1013,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D74FF93FCC3FC3CFC6CFB99" box="[841,903,1013,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by having a basal cymbial process (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D74FF93FA90FC3CFA8BFB99" box="[1306,1376,1013,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[164,1423,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2A–G. Patrera ruber (F. O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1900). Male (ICN-Ar-9674): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view (Arrow: indicates the basal cymbial process). Female (ICN- Ar-5353): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view (Arrow: indicates anterolateral notch of the lateral borders); G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 3mm; C: 1mm; 0.8mm D–E: 1mm; F–G: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468387/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs 2</figureCitation>
C–D; 8C–D; 
<bibRefCitation id="4455EB823D74FF93FF62FBD0FE20FBA5" author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[232,459,1049,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 187" refId="ref40616" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1997) Revis &quot; o de Anyphaeninae Bertkau a nivel de generos na regi &quot; o neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 13, 1 - 187." type="journal article" year="1997">Brescovit 1997: 147</bibRefCitation>
, figs 53–54), but can be distinguished by having small denticles on base of the embolus, extending to the apical region of the embolus and thin retrolateral tibial apophysis (wider in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FB2BFBF7FB14FBC1" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1185,1279,1085,1111]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimar">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FB2BFBF7FB14FBC1" box="[1185,1279,1085,1111]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. dimar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D74FF93FA92FBF4FAB1FBC1" box="[1304,1370,1085,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[164,1423,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2A–G. Patrera ruber (F. O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1900). Male (ICN-Ar-9674): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view (Arrow: indicates the basal cymbial process). Female (ICN- Ar-5353): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view (Arrow: indicates anterolateral notch of the lateral borders); G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 3mm; C: 1mm; 0.8mm D–E: 1mm; F–G: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468387/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C–E). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FE45FBABFDDBFBED" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[463,560,1121,1147]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimar">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FE45FBABFDDBFBED" box="[463,560,1121,1147]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. dimar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FDE0FBABFD0DFBED" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[618,742,1121,1147]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perafani" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FDE0FBABFD0DFBED" box="[618,742,1121,1147]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. perafani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FD65FBA8FCC4FBED" bold="true" box="[751,815,1121,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D74FF93FD65FBA8FCC4FBED" box="[751,815,1121,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by their shape of the ventral epigynal plate and large spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D74FF93FECAFB4CFE69FB09" box="[320,386,1157,1183]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-27@18.[151,1435,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 8A–G. Patrera dimar n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10634): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-10635): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C: 1mm; D–E 0.5mm; F–G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468399/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
F–G; 
<bibRefCitation id="4455EB823D74FF93FE4CFB4CFD06FB09" author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[454,749,1157,1183]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 187" refId="ref40616" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1997) Revis &quot; o de Anyphaeninae Bertkau a nivel de generos na regi &quot; o neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 13, 1 - 187." type="journal article" year="1997">Brescovit, 1997: 146–147</bibRefCitation>
, 55–56), but can be distinguished by their larger and thinner hood (wider in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FECAFB63FE76FB55" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[320,413,1193,1219]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimar">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FECAFB63FE76FB55" box="[320,413,1193,1219]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. dimar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FE58FB63FDA0FB55" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[466,587,1193,1219]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perafani">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FE58FB63FDA0FB55" box="[466,587,1193,1219]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. perafani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and lateral borders with a external notch on the anterolateral side (no notch in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D74FF93FF3EFB07FEF9FB71" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[180,274,1229,1255]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimar">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D74FF93FF3EFB07FEF9FB71" box="[180,274,1229,1255]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. dimar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D74FF93FEA1FB04FE86FB71" box="[299,365,1229,1255]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[164,1423,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2A–G. Patrera ruber (F. O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1900). Male (ICN-Ar-9674): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, ventral view; E palp, retrolateral view (Arrow: indicates the basal cymbial process). Female (ICN- Ar-5353): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view (Arrow: indicates anterolateral notch of the lateral borders); G epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 3mm; C: 1mm; 0.8mm D–E: 1mm; F–G: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468387/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
F–G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D74FF93FF4DFB38FC23FA9A" box="[199,968,1265,1292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
